CANNON FODDER, WINDOWS, AND MOUSE DRIVERS
-----------------------------------------
Although you may be able to run Cannon Fodder under Windows by
opening a DOS window, the software is designed to run under DOS.  We
recommend that you exit Windows completely before running the
software.  If you do run Cannon Fodder from Windows, please note
that the DOS mouse driver must be loaded.

DOS requires that a mouse driver is loaded before any program can
recognize the mouse.  Windows has a built-in mouse driver, but this
will not work in DOS.  Before you attempt to run Cannon Fodder make
sure the MOUSE.COM or MOUSE.EXE file is loaded.  These files are
provided on a disk that came with your mouse.  Check your DOS manual
if you don't how to load either file.

